<br>In the last 60 days the ability to correct your faction after being flagged as KOS was patched in. Last March Verant removed the ability to correct your faction once KOS because they felt too many people were taking advantage of the faction system and decided that once you killed Lucan and gained Soulfire, you should be forever KOS in WFP. I personally agree with this idea. But it seems someone thought it was a bad idea. So now you can correct your faction in places like GUK and WFP. Granted it will take forever, but it is possible.<br><br>Although I personal consider it an honour to be KOS to the Freeport militia, I realize some people play the game for different reasons. Therefor in the near future I will post some of the factions adjustment quests for Freeport Militia on my site. There are a handful of quests that will allow you to gain Freeport Militia faction without harming your NFP faction. And for those of you who have assisted me on the many Soulfire crusades, your faction is so high with NFP you could take a few hits and still be welcome in NFP no matter what.
	<br>
