While I bear no love for the Freeport milita, I do find that Freeport itself is the best place for me to develop and hone my trade skills, particularly Brewing and Smithing. It's the Druidic motto to "always be prepared" (at least I think that's where it came from...) so I have taken it upon myself to become a master at every possible skill I can.<br><br>There is one quest I know of that will give faction with the Freeport Milita without offending the Knights of Truth, it takes place in the city of Erudin. To do this quest, I believe you must have amiable faction with the Erudites (offing a few necros in Paineel will help this, while doing the world at large a favor as well). I can't remember the names at the moment, but it's a simple quest that involes talking to a man in the lobby area on the top floor of the Erudite castle, where all the casters hang out. He will give you something that you must take down to a man in the basement area near the bank in the Gem Shop I think. Doing this quest over and over will eventually boost your Freeport faction.<br><br>Although I really think that the best way to become nonKOS in Freeport is to simply pull orcs for newbies in EC. Not only does it give you faction, but the little guys will love you for it :)<br><br>Dourin Scimfeather<br>30th Season Druid of Tunare<br>"Hey buddy, think you could introduce me to your Guardian Spirit?"
