ACK!! You don't know who the Knights of Truth are?? Or the history of Sir Lucan??<br><br>Well, to sum it up bluntly.... Lucan WAS a Paladin, but turn to the darkside and is now a servant of evil. When you kill his "mortal form" (the militia looking guy), he respawns as an undead skeleton. It is from this corpse that our holy Paladins obtain proof of their valor and turn it in for the blade of Soulfire. <br><br>The hilt to Soulfire is obtained from Xicotl, big ugly Troll Shadow Knight in Castle MistMoore. After getting both of these pieces and a few other steps prior, the Paladin then must visit an NPC Pally that is imprisoned within SplitPaw and he will offer the completed weapon to the quester.<br><br>For more detailed information on the steps of this quest, please visit Avrohom's Paladin website at: <b><a href="http://trump9.tripod.com/paladin.html">http://trump9.tripod.com/paladin.html</a></b>  <--clickable link<br><br>In regards to the faction tables discussed here, by killing Sir Lucan you become KOS to the Freeport Militia which governs both West and East Freeport. The Knights of Truth still hold North Freeport as sanctuary. They report to the Hall of Truth and are true Paladins that stand against Sir Lucan and his Militia.<br><br>Hope this helps to clear the air for Pepi and others that might not know they "whys" of the Soulfire quest and why Aegis Lux supports it.<br><br>Thalador - The Surnameless<br>Officer<br>Co-Event Master<br><br><i>"I intend to live forever or die trying!!"</i><br>
